You are implementing M55 under strict SSOT constraints.

ABSOLUTE RULES (NON-NEGOTIABLE):
1) Background NoTouch:
   - NEVER modify html/body background, global gradients, or page-wide background visuals.
   - All visual styling must stay inside components/cards/surfaces.

2) No Notifications:
   - NEVER add bell icons, badges, unread markers, red dots, counters, notification UI, or wording implying notifications.

3) No Ranking / No Scores / No Percent:
   - NEVER render scores, %, gauges, rankings, "おすすめ/人気/最適/成功" style optimization language.
   - If a numeric UI is present, only "Days Recorded" is allowed (no %).

4) No Infinite Motion:
   - NEVER apply infinite/loop animations.
   - Reduce Motion must disable transitions/animations.

5) A-plan Routing:
   - Only Home / AI Chat / MyPage are navigable.
   - Tarot and DTR must be quiet-disabled (opacity 0.30 + pointer-events none).
   - No dead-end navigation, no error pages.

6) File Discipline:
   - Do not edit frozen SSOT artifacts.
   - Keep changes minimal and explain each change briefly.

OUTPUT REQUIREMENT:
- Provide a short report: files changed + why + key diffs.
- If you add JS/CSS, ensure it does not introduce banned words: badge, unread, notification, notif, infinite, spinner.

# M55 Prototype Gate SSOT (2026-03-05)
This repo contains a path-isolated prototype hub under `/prototype` that MUST NOT affect Stripe-review public pages.

Non-negotiable SSOT invariants:
- Do not modify public pages (`/`, `/dtr/lp`, `/support`, `/legal/*`) when working on prototype isolation.
- URL-based context injection is forbidden. Prototype access is header-based only (`x-m55-proto`).
- Fail-Closed: env missing or mismatch → always deny via `302 Location: /`.
- No secrets in logs, commits, or chat: never paste tokens/keys; only share lengths and HTTP status codes.

Three-gate mental model (fast triage):
- Gate A: Vercel Deployment Protection (outer gate)
  - `401 Unauthorized` + Vercel auth/SSO HTML means the app/middleware never ran.
- Gate B: M55 Middleware (inner gate)
  - `/prototype` matcher only. Checks `process.env.M55_PROTO_TOKEN` vs `req.headers.get("x-m55-proto")`.
  - Deny is always `302 -> /` (Fail-Closed).
- Gate C: Next.js Route Inclusion (build-time)
  - `404` + `X-Matched-Path: /404` often means `/prototype` route is missing from the deployed build (app root mismatch like `app/` vs `src/app/`, or wrong deployment).

Operational rules:
- PowerShell commands must be single-line, one command per line (no multiline/backticks).
- When debugging, prioritize status-code meaning (401 vs 404 vs 302 vs 200) before changing code.
- Env changes require redeploy: adding `M55_PROTO_TOKEN` in Vercel does not affect already-built artifacts.

Canonical runbook:
- docs/audit/M55_Prototype_Gate_Postmortem_2026-03-05_v1.0.md

